:: Followpath [Continue] {"position":"600,725","size":"100,100"}
<div class="Followchat">
You start to walk, well, more like dragging your feet. Every step feels like a strong force is pushing you backward, aiming to keep you where you are, instead of following.
 </div>

 <div class="Followchat">
You can't help but feel as if something is out of place. You lift your chin, wondering who this person you're speaking to, but you came face with nothing but an eerie, pit-black space, with only a few breeze creeping wiping your sweat. As you open your mouth to speak, a sudden sound, no, a music note, faintly brushes against your ear.
 </div>
 
    <span class="Leavebutton">
    (link-goto: "-->", "Leavespace")
  </span>
  
  
  <audio autoplay loop style ="display:none">
<source src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/WindyVG-Starter/Chicago-s_Song_Project/main/music/SadHospital.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
</audio>


:: Hospitalbed [Hospital hospitalbed] {"position":"1300,875","size":"100,100"}
 <div class="Beddialogue">
The moment you step your feet forward, the walls begin to scatter, rebuilding itself back up into a eerie, small room, with a single, yellow light shooting above the hospital bed. 
 </div>
 
  <div class="Beddialogue">
You hesitant, scanning the bedtable, full of flowers. A huge medical mechanic, beeping softly, and a rocking chair with a knitted blanket, suggests someone has been sleeping there, waiting.
 </div>
 
 
 
     </div>
 
 <div class="Yourbedroom_choices">
  
  <span class="Sleepbutton">
    (link-goto:  "Sleep in the bed" , "Sleep")
  </span>
  
    <span class="Nahbutton">
    (link-goto: "Wait" , "Nah")
  </span>
  
  </div>
  
</div>


:: Hospitalplace [hospitalplace] {"position":"1175,875","size":"100,100"}
 <div class="Beddialogue">
The moment the door opens, you are immediately surrounded in a cold, sterile, reflective hall. The same hospital that you ran from.
 </div>
 
 <div class="Beddialogue">
You freeze, feeling every chills creep up your arm. You stared into the abyss, permitting the darkness call out to you. You gulp, slowly stepping forward. Even though, you don't understand.
 </div>
 
 
      <span class="gochildhoodhomebutton ">
    (link-goto: "-->", "Hospitalbed")
  </span>


:: Leavespace [Leavespace] {"position":"725,725","size":"100,100"}
<div class="StoppingADippingchat">
You stop dead in your track, turning behind to meet nothing. However, you keep hearing  the music, softly echoing, yearning for a piece of your attention.
 </div>
 
 
 <div class="Voicechat">
Don't go, if you do. You will never want to leave.
 </div>
 
 <div class="StoppingADippingchat">
You continue to stare at the direction of the sound. With enough thought and gut, you rip away from pathway of the voice, jogging towards the ever growing music.
 </div>
 
 
    <span class="gochildhoodhomebutton ">
    (link-goto: "-->", "YourRoom")
  </span>
  
  
  <audio autoplay loop style ="display:none">
<source src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/WindyVG-Starter/Chicago-s_Song_Project/main/music/SadHospital.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
</audio>


:: Manuscriptpaper [Manu_script] {"position":"1050,600","size":"100,100"}
<div class=Manuscriptpaper1dialogue ">
You grabbed the manu script, and holy crap, it was a mess.
 </div>
 
<div class=Manuscriptpaper1dialogue ">
The longer you stares, the sooner, the music sheets becomes align, shaping them themselves into a language that flows effortlessly through your mind.
 </div>
 
 <div class=Manuscriptpaper1dialogue ">
In the corner of the script, a comment labeled by someone called "David''
 </div>
 
 <div class=Manuscriptpaper1dialogue ">
"Very common mistakes" David noted. "“You’ve ignored the fundamental logic of rhythmic grouping and beaming. Creatied the script unorganized and difficulted to read. Take your time."
 </div>
 
<div class=Manuscriptpaper1dialogue ">
Ah yes, David. The one good professor that offers good feedbacks, and often engages with his students. This university is known for large lecture halls, which is often hard for true one-on-one interaction, but he somehow makes it possible, often goes on his way to reach and email students. Some said he's doing too much, but I think he's doing enough.
 </div>
 
 
     </div>
 
 <div class="Yourbedroom_choices">
  
  <span class="_choices1">
    (link-goto:  "Photo frame" , "Photoframe")
  </span>
  
    <span class="_choices3">
    (link-goto: "Dorm Door" , "ExitDoor")
  </span>
  
  </div>
  
</div>


:: Nah [Nope] {"position":"1375,1025","size":"100,100"}
<div class="narrativedialogue">
In the end, there was nothing.
 </div>
 
 <div class="narrativedialogue">
Do you regret reliving this? Those memories, those people, and you? Do you want them? Do you want me to take them away? I can.
 </div>
 
  
      </div>
 
 <div class="Beddialogue">
  
  <span class="Nobutton">
    (link-goto:  ' "No. I want them"' , "No")
  </span>
  
    <span class="Yesbutton">
    (link-goto: ' "Yes. I dont need them"' , "Yes")
  </span>
  
  </div>
  
</div>


